# Chat profiles (separate conversations)

Long threads cause orchestrator drift. Use **new chats** for distinct job types instead of one mega-thread.

| Chat profile | Open when | Skills / rules | Stop when |
|--------------|-----------|----------------|-----------|
| **BA initiative** | Discovery, debrief, `/status`, `/next`, slicing, retro | ba-assistant (lazy), meeting-debrief | Task done — new chat for next task |
| **Confluence / Jira publish** | Publish status, create tickets | publish-docs-to-confluence, fcm-jira-templates | Page/ticket live |
| **Quick ask** | One factual question, no initiative state | Skip BA orchestrator | Answered |

## Resume discipline

- **Same initiative, new task** → new chat + first message: `BA resume — [task]` (triggers Step 2.75)
- **Mid-thread drift** → `/reanchor` or new chat (prefer new chat if >30 turns)
- **Never** rely on conversation summary alone — sessionStart hook injects SESSION-CONTEXT tail; agent must still Read full file on BA-resume

## Workspace note

Multi-root workspaces are supported. Classify the user's intent, not which folder is open.
